name: 12. The Valley of Death.
description:
"Once down here the sounds of a hundred different birds would fill the morning air. Frogs at night, with their choral chirping. In the days you could spot wallabies, when our dogs weren't tearing through making a ruckus and scaring them back to their little Wallaby abodes. Everything now seemed eerily quiet, only crackling and the occasional crash of falling trees. Smoke lingered and ash drifted hauntingly on the breeze. This was no longer a valley of brimming life and green. Just black and grey, silence."

Photography by Jay Moon, during the Australian wildfires; November 2019.
#12 of 15.
All funds generated go toward the ongoing recovery.
